ODE IX.

Tms is a drinking song for the winter, imitated from an Ode of Alcaeus. A party is supposed to be assembled in the city, and one calls upon the master of the feast to bring out his best wine, and make the fire burn bright, that they may banish care and all thought for the future, since youth is the time for innocent enjoyment.
